## installing additional utilities
   
    # pacman -S A B C... X Y Z

some suggested packages.

    parted
    iproute2
    neovim/nano
    less
    man-db
    man-pages
    sudo
    systemd-resolvconf
    zsh

- Set the time zone:

    # ln -sf /usr/share/zoneinfo/Region/City /etc/localtime

Run `hwclock` to generate /etc/adjtime:

    # hwclock --systohc

- generate needed locales 

e.g. edit /etc/locale.gen and uncomment `en_US.UTF-8` and `fr_CA.UTF-8`. Then generate the locales.

    # locale-gen

Create the `/etc/locale.conf` file, and set the LANG variable accordingly:

    LANG=en_US.UTF-8

If you set the keyboard layout, make the changes persistent in `/etc/vconsole.conf`

    /etc/vconsole.conf

    KEYMAP=de-latin1

